variants.name: Default Configuration
variants.description:
enabled: indicates whether the circuit breaker is enabled 

failureRateThreshold: The failure rate percentage at which the circuit breaker will open

failureExecutionThreshold: the minimum number of consecutive failures required to execute before the circuit breaker opens/trips

failureThresholdPeriod: the minimum amount of time in which the failure threshold is measured

delayPeriod: the amount of time the circuit breaker remains open before moving to the half-opened state

successThreshold: the number of consecutive successful executions required to transition from the half-open state to the closed state
